import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['co2_concentration'], label='CO2 Concentration')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_average = data.groupby('Year')['CO2'].mean().reset_index()

    ax = yearly_average.plot.bar(x='Year', y='CO2', legend=False, figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average CO2 Concentration')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['co2_concentration'] = pd.to_numeric(data['co2_concentration'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['co2_concentration'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['co2_concentration'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='CO2 Concentration')
    plt.axvline(data['co2_concentration'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['co2_concentration'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['co2_concentration'], data['temperature'])
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 concentration and temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['CO2 Concentration vs Temperature'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    data['Month'] = data['Date'].dt.month
    data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.groupby(['Year', 'Month'])['CO2'].mean().unstack().plot(ax=ax)
    
    plt.title('What is the seasonal variation in CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.legend(title='Month', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
